<p><strong>Final ThoughtsÂ </strong></p>

<p>I believe the above process worked because I started with a standard upgrade as the install (as opposed to an archive and install). Iâ€™m not sure how successful this recovery process would have been had I performed a different install initially. The moral of the story is that you should always back up prior to doing an install of a new OS. I have one more installation to do tomorrow on a work computer and weâ€™ll see if I take my own advice.</p>

